    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve factors achieved the required gradation level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required level of 3; this gap is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent establishing ASTM F1717 compression-bending as the primary and sufficient test modality for pedicle screw submissions. All three QoIs satisfied quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; MAPE < 10%). The FEA model is accepted as credible for the stated COU.",
